        <div id="media-content-block_5a09b12e8dee41eaaea8fc09c1ca5637" class="media-content alignfull no-bottom-content hjs-section has-title no-bg dark">
          <div class="wrap">
            <div class="title-wrap">
              <h2 class="section-title">What’s Your Reason to Pour?</h2>
              <div class="section-description">
                <p>Many factors contribute to bad breath, but SmartMouth™’s zinc ion technology provides THE solution to stop bad breath at the source and prevent it from coming back for 24 hours. Learn how below!</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="blocks">
              <div id="media-content-block_5a09b12e8dee41eaaea8fc09c1ca5637-row1" class="media-content-wrap left fifty image">
                <div class="media-wrap" data-aos="fade-right">
                  <img loading="lazy" width="711" height="712" src="https://www.smartmouth.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/causes.jpg" alt="causes">
                </div>
                <div class="content-wrap" data-aos="fade-left">
                  <h2>Causes of Bad Breath</h2>
                  <p>Everyone experiences bad breath because it’s a naturally occurring process. Our mouths can contain billions of germs, and these bacteria break down protein particles in our saliva or near our gum line. When they do, they produce foul-smelling sulfur gas, otherwise known as bad breath.</p>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div id="media-content-block_5a09b12e8dee41eaaea8fc09c1ca5637-row2" class="media-content-wrap right fifty image">
                <div class="media-wrap" data-aos="fade-left">
                  <img loading="lazy" width="1030" height="852" src="https://www.smartmouth.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/ZincTech-1030x852.jpg" alt="ZincTech">
                </div>
                <div class="content-wrap" data-aos="fade-right">
                  <h2>You Activate the Zinc Ions</h2>
                  <p>When the two solutions come together, a chemical reaction occurs that instantly releases billions of zinc ions.</p>
                  <p>When you first pour the rinse, you’ll notice it’s green. That means the solution is freshly activated and the zinc ions are ready to bind to germs.</p>
                  <p>But, if you wait 5 minutes after pouring, you’ll notice the poured mouthwash turns blue. That means the zinc ions are no longer as effective at preventing bad breath.</p>
                  <p>So remember, always use SmartMouth™ immediately after pouring!</p>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div id="media-content-block_5a09b12e8dee41eaaea8fc09c1ca5637-row3" class="media-content-wrap left fifty image">
                <div class="media-wrap" data-aos="fade-right">
                  <img loading="lazy" width="1030" height="852" src="https://www.smartmouth.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/24Hours-1030x852.jpg" alt="24 Hour Mouthwash">
                </div>
                <div class="content-wrap" data-aos="fade-left">
                  <h2>Two Rinses a Day Keeps Bad Breath Away</h2>
                  <p>SmartMouth™ Mouthwash doesn’t mask bad breath. It stops it at the source.</p>
                  <p>Preventative care is the key to overcoming the problem of bad breath, and SmartMouth™ is the way to achieve real, lasting results.</p>
                  <p>Just two rinses a day will put your worries about embarrassing bad breath to rest and allow you to feel confident about getting up close.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

